Aim
To install and configure the Metasploitable vulnerable machine using Vagrant and verify communication with
Kali Linux.
Introduction
Metasploitable is a deliberately vulnerable Linux virtual machine used for penetration testing practice. It is
commonly used with Kali Linux to learn vulnerability scanning and exploitation techniques.
Procedure
Step 1: Create Working Directory
mkdir metasploitable-lab
cd metasploitable-lab
Step 2: Initialize Metasploitable Box
vagrant init rapid7/metasploitable3-ub1404
Step 3: Start Metasploitable VM
vagrant up
Step 4: Access Metasploitable
vagrant ssh
Step 5: Verify Network Communication
From Kali Linux terminal, ping the Metasploitable machine:
ping 192.168.56.101
Step 6: Analyze Connectivity
Observe successful ICMP reply packets.
Output
64 bytes from 192.168.56.101
Host reachable
Result
Thus, the Metasploitable vulnerable machine was installed successfully and communication with Kali Linux
was verified
